casebody.data:
Jeffery D. OVERBECK, Petitioner/Appellant
v.
Amy L. OVERBECK, Respondent. No. ED 105341 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION FOUR. FILED: June 5, 2018 FOR APPELLANT: Alexa C. Hart-Lorenz, Adam R. Lorenz-co-counsel, 339 Broadway, Suite 110, Cape Girardeau, Missouri 63701. FOR RESPONDENT: John D. Moore, P.O. Box 1027, Sikeston, Missouri 63801. Before Colleen Dolan, P.J., Mary K. Hoff, J., Lisa S. Van Amburg, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

Jeffery Overbeck appeals the trial court's dissolution judgment as it relates to child support following his divorce from Amy Overbeck. We affirm.

We have reviewed the briefs of the parties and the record on appeal and find no error of law. No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. However, the parties have been furnished with a memorandum opinion for their information only, setting forth the facts and reasons for this order.

The judgment of the trial court is affirmed in accordance with Rule 84.16(b).
